“on that duty” are substituted for the words “so serving”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idab8ef720-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1958 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Act","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The change is necessary to make subsection (d) coextensive with subsection (c), to which it was a proviso in the source law, the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1916-06-03"},"text":"June 3, 1916","children":[],"tail":", chapter 134, section 5 (1st sentence of 2d par.) (formerly "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s38"},"text":"10 U.S.C. 38","children":[],"tail":" (1st sentence of 2d par.))."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab8ef721-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab8ef722-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Subsec. (b)(2), (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s516/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 516(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “not on active duty” after “United States” in par. (2) and after “Army Reserve” in par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s516/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 516(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “of the reserve components” after “among the members” and struck out “not on active duty” before period at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3021"},"text":"section 3021 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/433/s501/a/8/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–433, § 501(a)(8)(C)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3033"},"text":"section 3033 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section, and substituted “Army Reserve Forces Policy Committee” for “Reserve components of Army; policies and regulations for government of” in section catchline."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/433/s501/a/8/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–433, § 501(a)(8)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Office” for “office” and “Committee. The Committee” for “Committee which”, inserted “and the mobilization preparedness”, and substituted “Army. The” for “Army, and the” and “Secretary of the Army and the Chief of Staff” for “Chief of Staff and the Assistant Secretary responsible for reserve affairs”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/433/s501/a/8/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–433, § 501(a)(8)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “General” before “Staff” in two places."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1967—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/168"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–168","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally, and restated with certain changes the existing authority relating to the Army Reserve Forces Policy Committee within the Office of the Secretary of the Army, reduced the membership of the Committee from 21 to 15, reduced the grade requirements so as to permit inclusion of colonels, and provided that the Committee review and comment upon all major policies affecting Army Reserve matters and that the Committee comments accompany any final submission to the Chief of Staff and Assistant Secretary responsible for Reserve Affairs."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1958—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/861"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–861","children":[],"tail":" substituted “affecting the organization, distribution, training, appointment, assignment, promotion, or discharge of members of the Army Reserve and those of either” for “affecting the Army Reserve and either”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idab8ef723-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab8ef724-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1967 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/168"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–168","children":[],"tail":" effective on first day of first calendar month following date of enactment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/168"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–168","children":[],"tail":", which was approved "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1967-12-01"},"text":"Dec. 1, 1967","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/168/s7"},"text":"section 7 of Pub. L. 90–168","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s138"},"text":"section 138 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab8ef725-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"t